    <p> Earthquakes are the shaking of the earth's surface caused by a sudden release of energy in the lithosphere that creates seismic waves </p>
    <p> The lithosphere is the layer of earth comprised of the crust and the uppermost part of the mantle</p>
    <p> Other name for earthquakes</p>
    <p> Quake: The general name for this phenomenon as quakes on moon are referred to as moonquakes and on mars they are marsquakes so on earth its earthquakes</p>
    <p> Tremor: The word tremor may also be used for non-earthquake seismic rumbles</p>
